# Phase 35.5 · Makefile, CI, and Maintenance Validation

Repository: `cvsz/zdash`

Execution profile: DeepSeek V4 Flash Free / fast free coding model.

Goal:
Finalize local validation, Makefile safety scans, CI workflow sanity, and Codex Cloud maintenance checks for zDash release readiness.

This pass focuses on validation infrastructure. Do not make product feature changes.

---

## Safety invariants

- Do not commit `.env`, secrets, tokens, GPG passphrases, private keys, local caches, node_modules, dist, or local Codex run artifacts.
- `docs/prompts/codex-runs/` must remain local-only and untracked.
- Backend port is `8005`; do not introduce `localhost:8000` or `BACKEND_PORT=8000` in tracked runtime/source files.
- Safety scans must avoid self-scan false positives from their own scanner patterns.
- Safety scans should inspect tracked runtime/source files, not ignored caches.
- Do not weaken safety policy just to pass validation.

---

## Inspect first

Inspect:

```text
Makefile
.gitignore
.github/workflows/
.codex/cloud/README.md
.codex/cloud/phase-runner.md
.codex/cloud/maintenance.sh
.codex/cloud/setup.sh
.codex/cloud/repair-backend-deps.sh
.env.example
frontend/.env.example
backend/pyproject.toml
frontend/package.json
docker-compose.yml
docker-compose.prod.yml
infra/docker/
infra/nginx/
```

Create an inspection summary:

```text
- Make targets present
- safety scan behavior
- ignored local-only files
- CI workflow coverage
- maintenance script behavior
- Docker build targets
- compose config status
- false-positive risks
```

---

## Required Makefile behavior

Verify targets exist and behave:

```text
make help
make safety-scan
make backend-lint
make backend-test
make backend-check
make frontend-test
make frontend-build
make frontend-check
make validate-fast
make docker-build
make compose-check
make maintenance
make validate
```

### safety-scan must check

```text
forbidden tracked files
.env formatting without printing values
old backend port 8000 references in tracked runtime/source files
secret-looking values in tracked runtime/source files
```

### safety-scan must not fail on

```text
Makefile scanner command text
.codex/cloud scanner command text
ignored caches
node_modules
.venv
frontend/dist
backend/.pytest_cache
backend/.ruff_cache
docs/prompts/codex-runs/ when untracked/ignored
```

If false positives occur, patch the scanner to exclude self-files or ignored/generated paths while preserving the actual safety check.

---

## Git ignore policy

Verify ignored/local-only paths:

```text
.env
.env.*.local
frontend/.env.local
.agent/
.agents/
.claude/
.gemini/
.mcp/
.venv/
backend/.venv/
node_modules/
frontend/node_modules/
frontend/dist/
backend/zdash.db
backups/
docs/prompts/codex-runs/
.codex/reports/
.codex/runs/
```

If a forbidden local-only file is tracked, untrack it with:

```bash
git rm --cached <path>
```

Do not delete the user’s local copy unless explicitly required.

---

## CI workflow sanity

Inspect `.github/workflows/` and verify it covers:

```text
backend lint/tests
frontend tests/build
Docker build sanity
security scan if present
Pages/deploy jobs if present
```

Do not add expensive or flaky jobs unless clearly required.

---

## Maintenance script

Verify `.codex/cloud/maintenance.sh`:

- uses development-safe env overrides where needed
- does not fail on its own scanner text
- does not expose secrets
- records a report under `.codex/reports/`
- exits non-zero only for real failures in strict mode
- supports advisory mode if already implemented

Patch only clear issues.

---

## Validation sequence

Run in order and stop at the first real failure:

```bash
cd ~/zdash
make safety-scan
```

```bash
cd ~/zdash
APP_ENV=development \
DATABASE_URL=sqlite:///./zdash_test.db \
PRODUCTION_SAFETY_LOCK=true \
DRY_RUN=true \
LIVE_TRADING_ACK=false \
make validate-fast
```

If Docker is available:

```bash
cd ~/zdash
APP_ENV=development \
DATABASE_URL=sqlite:///./zdash_test.db \
PRODUCTION_SAFETY_LOCK=true \
DRY_RUN=true \
LIVE_TRADING_ACK=false \
make validate
```

If Docker is unavailable, report that Docker validation was skipped.

---

## Non-blocking known warnings

Not blockers if summaries pass:

```text
passlib crypt deprecation warning from dependency
React act(...) warnings in existing hook tests
React Router future flag warnings
intentional ErrorBoundary test Error: fail
Vite chunk size warning
```

Blocking:

```text
ruff failure
pytest failure
vitest failed tests
TypeScript build failure
safety-scan failure
Docker build failure when Docker is available
compose config failure
tracked forbidden files
tracked secret-like values
tracked port 8000 runtime/source references
```

---

## Allowed changes

Allowed:

- Makefile scanner fixes
- .gitignore fixes
- CI workflow minor validation fixes
- maintenance script false-positive fixes
- docs updates about validation
- untracking forbidden local-only files

Not allowed:

- product feature changes
- weakening safety scans
- adding live trading
- committing local-only artifacts
- hiding real failures as warnings

---

